stnStackingRuleProtocol.name: stnStackingRuleProtocol

stnStackingRuleTunnelType.description: The tunneling action the connection will take if the rule comparison protocol is matched.

stnStackingRuleTunnelEndPoint.description: The name of server endpoint that we will TunnelType to when the rule comparison protocol is matched.

stnEndPointEntry.name: stnEndPointEntry

stnEndPointIndex.description: The configuration instance of this endpoint.

stnEndPointName.description: The name of server endpoint - if no address is configured then this name will be used for a DNS lookup

stnEndPointPassword.name: stnEndPointPassword
stnEndPointPassword.description: The challenge password or shared secret for this endpoint.

stnAddressPoolEntry.name: stnAddressPoolEntry

stnStartIpAddress.description: The starting IP address of the address range

stnEndIpAddress.name: stnEndIpAddress
stnEndIpAddress.description: The ending IP address of the address range

stnNetworkAccessUserAuthenType.name: stnNetworkAccessUserAuthenType
stnNetworkAccessUserAuthenType.description: The type of authentication that will be performed for all users using the router - only one user authentication type may be specified at a time

stnNetworkAccessEndPointAuthenType.name: stnNetworkAccessEndPointAuthenType
stnNetworkAccessEndPointAuthenType.description: The type of authentication that will be performed for all endpoints using the router - only one endpoint authentication type may be specified at a time

stnNetworkAccessUserAccType.name: stnNetworkAccessUserAccType
stnNetworkAccessUserAccType.description: The type of accounting that will be performed for all users using the router - more than one user authentication may be specified at a time

stnNetworkAccessEndPointAccType.name: stnNetworkAccessEndPointAccType
stnNetworkAccessEndPointAccType.description: The type of accounting that will be performed for all endpoints using the router - more than one endpoint authentication may be specified at a time

stnNetworkAccessDomainName.name: stnNetworkAccessDomainName
stnNetworkAccessDomainName.description: The domain name configured for the router - this domain name is used primarily for PPPOE when no router can be determined from the connection type - a username parse will occur attempting to match this domain name with a string located after an '@' sign in the user name ex: john@springtidenetworks.com

stnNetworkAccessServiceNameRadiusAttrTyp.name: stnNetworkAccessServiceNameRadiusAttrType
stnNetworkAccessServiceNameRadiusAttrTyp.description: The type of RADIUS attribute that will be used to carry the service name for a user if applicable

stnNetworkAccessLdapAuthorizationUpdateT.name: stnNetworkAccessLdapAuthorizationUpdateTime
stnNetworkAccessLdapAuthorizationUpdateT.description: The amount of time between LDAP updates for this router in seconds

stnNetworkAccessLdapUpdateNotification.name: stnNetworkAccessLdapUpdateNotification
stnNetworkAccessLdapUpdateNotification.description: LDAP service update notification from network management apps.

stnNetworkAccessRealmAttrType.name: stnNetworkAccessRealmAttrType
stnNetworkAccessRealmAttrType.description: The type of RADIUS attribute that will be used to specify the realm name for a user if applicable

stnRadiusAccServerEntry.name: stnRadiusAccServerEntry
stnRadiusAccServerEntry.description: An Radius Accounting Server entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single radius accounting server entry

stnRadiusAccServerIndex.name: stnRadiusAccServerIndex
stnRadiusAccServerIndex.description: The priority of this accounting server - higher priority servers will attempt to be contacted before lower priority servers - highest priority is 1 - priority indexes must be contiguous

stnRadiusAccServerAddress.name: stnRadiusAccServerAddress
stnRadiusAccServerAddress.description: The IP address of this Radius accounting server.

stnRadiusAccServerDestPort.name: stnRadiusAccServerDestPort
stnRadiusAccServerDestPort.description: The destination accounting port of this Radius accounting server.

stnRadiusAccServerRetrans.name: stnRadiusAccServerRetrans
stnRadiusAccServerRetrans.description: The number of times the router will attempt to retransmit to this server if there is no response

stnRadiusAccServerTimeOut.name: stnRadiusAccServerTimeOut
stnRadiusAccServerTimeOut.description: The time in seconds to determine the last (re)transmission to this server failed.

stnRadiusAccServerSecret.name: stnRadiusAccServerSecret
stnRadiusAccServerSecret.description: The shared secret configured for this Radius accounting server - this secret must also be configured on the RADIUS server itself

stnRadiusAccServerName.name: stnRadiusAccServerName
stnRadiusAccServerName.description: The name of this Radius accounting server - this name will be used for a DNS lookup if an ip address is not configured

stnRadiusAccServerConfigInstance.name: stnRadiusAccServerConfigInstance
stnRadiusAccServerConfigInstance.description: The configuration instance of this accounting server

stnRadiusAuthServerIndex.description: The priority of this Radius authentication server - highest priority is 1 and higher priority servers will be contacted first - the priorities must be contiguous

stnRadiusAuthServerAddress.name: stnRadiusAuthServerAddress
stnRadiusAuthServerAddress.description: The IP address of this Radius authentication server.

stnRadiusAuthServerDestPort.name: stnRadiusAuthServerDestPort
stnRadiusAuthServerDestPort.description: The destination authenticaton port of this Radius authentication server.

stnRadiusAuthServerRetrans.name: stnRadiusAuthServerRetrans
stnRadiusAuthServerRetrans.description: The number of times the router will attempt to retransmit to this radius authentication server

stnRadiusAuthServerTimeOut.name: stnRadiusAuthServerTimeOut
stnRadiusAuthServerTimeOut.description: The time (in seconds) to determine the last (re)transmission to this authentication server failed.

stnRadiusAuthServerSecret.name: stnRadiusAuthServerSecret
stnRadiusAuthServerSecret.description: The shared secret configured for this Radius authentication server - this same secret must be configured on the RADIUS server itself

stnRadiusAuthServerName.name: stnRadiusAuthServerName
stnRadiusAuthServerName.description: The name of this Radius authentication server - this name will be used for a DNS lookup if no ip address is configured

stnRadiusAuthServerConfigInstance.name: stnRadiusAuthServerConfigInstance
stnRadiusAuthServerConfigInstance.description: The configuration instance of this Radius authentication server

stnUserEntry.name: stnUserEntry
stnUserEntry.description: An User entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single user entry

stnUserIndex.name: stnUserIndex
stnUserIndex.description: The configuration instance of this entry.

stnUserName.name: stnUserName
stnUserName.description: The user name for this user table entry

stnUserIpAddress.name: stnUserIpAddress
stnUserIpAddress.description: The IP address for user sessions created for this user - 255.255.255.254 picks an address from the address pool table and 0 or 255.255.255.255 allows the user to pick the address.

stnUserIpNetMask.name: stnUserIpNetMask
stnUserIpNetMask.description: The IP sub-network mask for sessions created for this user.

stnUserIpRouting.name: stnUserIpRouting
stnUserIpRouting.description: The routing method for this user session.

stnUserMTU.name: stnUserMTU
stnUserMTU.description: The maximum transmission unit used by the framed protocol that this user is configured for.

stnUserIpCompression.name: stnUserIpCompression
stnUserIpCompression.description: The compression type for sessions created for this user.

stnUserTimeOut.name: stnUserTimeOut
stnUserTimeOut.description: The total amount of time a session should be allowed to stay connected. A value of 0 indicates no timeout

stnUserIdleTime.name: stnUserIdleTime
stnUserIdleTime.description: The total amount of time a session should be allowed to stay connected when idle. A value of 0 indicates no timeout

stnUserTunnelType.name: stnUserTunnelType
stnUserTunnelType.description: The type of tunnel that should be used for compulsory tunneling - none indicates that this user should be given a strictly PPP session

stnUserTunnelServerEndPoint.name: stnUserTunnelServerEndPoint
stnUserTunnelServerEndPoint.description: The name of the tunnel server endpoint to be used when a valid tunnel type is configured

stnUserTunnelClientEndPoint.name: stnUserTunnelClientEndPoint
stnUserTunnelClientEndPoint.description: The name of the tunnel client endpoint to be used when a valid tunnel type is configured

stnUserAssignedTunnelName.name: stnUserAssignedTunnelName
stnUserAssignedTunnelName.description: The name of the tunnel initiator to which a session is to be assigned - this variable allows for a grouping mechanism of tunnel sessions

stnUserTunnelPassword.name: stnUserTunnelPassword
stnUserTunnelPassword.description: The shared secret used for this tunnel session when a valid tunnel type is configured

stnUserServiceType.name: stnUserServiceType
stnUserServiceType.description: The permission level of the user - framed indicates a PPP user and possibly a tunnel user, login indicates a telnet or serial user with read-only allowances, provisioner indicates a telnet or serial user with read-only allowances as well as write privileges for the specific router they are configured on, administrative indicates a telent or serial user with read-only allowances as well as write priveleges for all routers

stnUserIpFilters.name: stnUserIpFilters
stnUserIpFilters.description: The list of IP filters that this user entry will be using for its sessions - every four bytes of the octet string contain a 32 bit filter configuration instance

stnUserIpRoutes.name: stnUserIpRoutes
stnUserIpRoutes.description: The list of IP routes for this user - every four bytes of the octet string contain a 32 bit route configuration instance

stnUserPrimaryDNSServer.name: stnUserPrimaryDNSServer
stnUserPrimaryDNSServer.description: The IP address of the primary DNS server

stnUserSecondaryDNSServer.name: stnUserSecondaryDNSServer

stnUserRealmInstance.description: The instance of this users Realm record

stnDefaultUserIpNetMask.description: The IP sub-network mask that the PPP default user will use.

stnMaxUserSessionLimitExceeded.name: stnMaxUserSessionLimitExceeded
stnMaxUserSessionLimitExceeded.description: A stnMaxUserSessionLimitExceeded trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the maximum number of sessions has been exceeded on one of its engines. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the AAATraps configuration object.

stnRadiusAuthenMismatch.name: stnRadiusAuthenMismatch
stnRadiusAuthenMismatch.description: A stnRadiusAuthenMismatch trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the a authentication failure (security breach or retransmission parameter) has been detected on one of its routers. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the AAATraps configuration object.

stnPrimaryBillingServerFailure.name: stnPrimaryBillingServerFailure
stnPrimaryBillingServerFailure.description: A stnPrimaryBillingServerFailure trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that a problem has occurred with the primary billing server and is switching to a secondary billing server. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the AAATraps configuration object.

stnNoAddressesAvailable.name: stnNoAddressesAvailable
stnNoAddressesAvailable.description: A stnNoAddressesAvailable trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that no addresses are available on the indicated router. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the AAATraps configuration object.
